{
  "output": "@startuml
actor Player
participant GameSystem

note right of Player: Rule 1
Player -> GameSystem: Enter names
alt Name is "Computer"
  GameSystem -> Player: "Name cannot be Computer"
  note right of GameSystem: Rule 17
  Player -> GameSystem: Enter valid name
end

GameSystem -> GameSystem: Initialize points to 0 for all players
note right of GameSystem: Rule 2

GameSystem -> GameSystem: Randomize player order
note right of GameSystem: Rule 16

loop 12 times or until game ends
  Player -> GameSystem: Decide to skip turn?
  note right of Player: Rule 20
  alt Player skips turn
    GameSystem -> GameSystem: Skip to next player
  else Player does not skip
    Player -> GameSystem: Throw dice
    note right of Player: Rule 4
    alt Dice count is 1
      Player -> GameSystem: Decide to re-roll?
      note right of Player: Rule 9
      alt Player re-rolls
        Player -> GameSystem: Throw dice again
      end
    end
    alt Dice count is 2
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Triple dice count
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 14
    else Dice count is even but not 2
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Halve dice count
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 14
    else Dice count is 5
      Player -> GameSystem: Throw dice again
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Multiply both dice counts
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 18
    end
    GameSystem -> GameSystem: Add dice count to player's points
    note right of GameSystem: Rule 5
    alt Player throws a 6
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Skip next player's turn
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 13
    end
    alt Player throws same value three times
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Reset player's points to 0
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 21
    end
    alt Player's points > 5
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Change point color to yellow
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 19
    end
    alt Player's points > 11
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Change point color to purple
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 12
    end
    GameSystem -> Player: Print dice count and player points
    note right of GameSystem: Rule 6
    alt Points are equal
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: Print "Equality!"
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 15
    end
    alt One player has 10 more points than others
      GameSystem -> GameSystem: End game
      note right of GameSystem: Rule 8
    end
  end
end

alt Game ends
  GameSystem -> GameSystem: Print players' points and winner
  note right of GameSystem: Rule 23
  alt Players decide to play again
    GameSystem -> GameSystem: Order players by last game's points ascending
    note right of GameSystem: Rule 25
  end
end

GameSystem -> Player: "Congratulations " + player name + " you won the game! You are the best!"
note right of GameSystem: Rule 10
@enduml"
}

actor User
participant Game
participant Board
participant Paddle
participant Ball
participant Brick

note right of Game: Rule 1
User -> Game: Start Game
Game -> Board: Initialize Board
note right of Board: Rule 2
Game -> Ball: Initialize Ball
note right of Ball: Rule 3
Game -> Paddle: Initialize Paddle
note right of Paddle: Rule 11
Game -> Brick: Initialize Bricks
note right of Brick: Rule 10

loop Each Level
  Game -> Ball: Start Ball Movement
  note right of Ball: Rule 4
  loop While Level Not Complete
    User -> Paddle: Move Paddle
    note right of Paddle: Rule 5
    Ball -> Paddle: Check Collision
    alt Ball Hits Paddle
      Ball -> Ball: Change Direction
      note right of Ball: Rule 12
    end
    Ball -> Brick: Check Collision
    alt Ball Hits Brick
      Brick -> Ball: Change Direction
      note right of Ball: Rule 12
      Brick -> Brick: Reduce Brick Strength
      alt Brick Destroyed
        Brick -> Game: Update Score
      end
    end
    alt Ball Falls Off Bottom
      Ball -> Game: Lose Life
      note right of Game: Rule 17
      alt Lives Remaining
        Game -> Board: Restart Level
        note right of Board: Rule 18
      else
        Game -> User: Game Over
        note right of Game: Rule 18
        User -> Game: Play Again?
        alt User Wants to Play Again
          Game -> Game: Restart Game
          note right of Game: Rule 19
        else
          Game -> Game: End Game
        end
      end
    end
  end
  Game -> Game: Level Complete
  note right of Game: Rule 6
  Game -> Board: Initialize Next Level
  note right of Board: Rule 14
  Game -> Ball: Increase Speed
  note right of Ball: Rule 13
end

  Game -> Ball: Set Ball Position (Top Left)

  Game -> Ball: Set Ball Trajectory (45° angle)
  Game -> Paddle: Reset Paddle Position (Center Bottom)
  note right of Paddle: Rule 11
  Game -> Brick: Generate Brick Pattern
  note right of Brick: Rule 15
  alt Level 1
    Game -> Brick: Place 50 Blue Single Bricks
    note right of Brick: Rule 10
  else Next Levels
    Game -> Brick: Add 2 Red Bricks, 1 Gold Brick
    note right of Brick: Rule 14
  end
end

loop While Level Not Complete
  User -> Paddle: Move Paddle (Left/Right)
  note right of Paddle: Rule 11
  Ball -> Paddle: Check Collision
  alt Ball Hits Paddle
    Ball -> Ball: Change Direction (Reflect)
    note right of Ball: Rule 12
  end
  Ball -> Brick: Check Collision
  alt Ball Hits Brick
    Brick -> Ball: Change Direction (Reflect)
    note right of Ball: Rule 12
    Brick -> Brick: Update Brick State
    alt Blue Brick
      Brick -> Brick: Destroy Brick
      note right of Brick: Rule 9
    else Red Brick
      Brick -> Brick: Decrease Hit Count
      note right of Brick: Rule 9
    else Gold Brick
      Brick -> Brick: Decrease Hit Count
      note right of Brick: Rule 9
    end
  end
  Ball -> Board: Check Collision
  alt Ball Hits Border
    Ball -> Ball: Change Direction (Reflect)
    note right of Ball: Rule 12
  else Ball Falls Off Bottom
    User -> Game: Lose Life
    note right of Game: Rule 17
    alt Lives Remaining
      Game -> Game: Restart Level
      note right of Game: Rule 18
    else No Lives Remaining
      Game -> User: Game Over
      note right of Game: Rule 18
      User -> Game: Play Again?
      alt User Wants to Play Again
        Game -> Game: Restart Game (Level 1)
        note right of Game: Rule 19
      else User Does Not Want to Play Again
        Game -> Game: End Game
        note right of Game: Rule 19
      end
    end
  end
end

  Game -> Game: Start Next Level
  note right of Game: Rule 14
  Game -> Ball: Increase Ball Speed
  note right of Ball: Rule 13
end
@enduml"

{
  "output": "@startuml

participant Brick

note right of Game: Rule 1
User -> Game: Start Game

note right of Ball: Rule 3
Game -> Paddle: Initialize Paddle (20x10 pixels)
Game -> Brick: Initialize Bricks (20x10 or 40x10 pixels)
note right of Brick: Rule 3

loop for each level (1 to 33)
  Game -> Ball: Set Ball Start Position (Top Left)
  note right of Ball: Rule 4
  Game -> Ball: Set Ball Speed (5 pixels/sec + level)
  note right of Ball: Rule 13
  Game -> Paddle: Reset Paddle to Center
  note right of Paddle: Rule 11
  Game -> Brick: Generate Random Brick Pattern
  note right of Brick: Rule 15
  alt First Level
    Game -> Brick: Initialize 50 Blue Single Bricks
    note right of Brick: Rule 10
  else Other Levels
    Game -> Brick: Add 2 Red Bricks, 1 Gold Brick
    note right of Brick: Rule 14
  end

  loop while level not completed
    User -> Paddle: Move Paddle (Left/Right)
    note right of Paddle: Rule 11
    Ball -> Board: Check Collision with Borders
    alt Collision with Paddle or Border
      Ball -> Ball: Change Direction
      note right of Ball: Rule 12
    else Collision with Bottom Border
      Game -> User: Lose Life
      note right of User: Rule 17
      alt Lives Remaining
        Game -> Level: Restart Level
        note right of Level: Rule 18
      else No Lives Remaining
        Game -> User: Game Over
        note right of User: Rule 18
        User -> Game: Decide to Play Again?
        alt Play Again
          Game -> Level: Restart from Level 1
          note right of Level: Rule 19
        else End Game
          note right of Game: Rule 19
        end
      end
    end

    Ball -> Brick: Check Collision with Bricks
    alt Collision with Brick
      Brick -> Brick: Reduce Brick Strength
      note right of Brick: Rule 9
      alt Brick Destroyed
        Brick -> Game: Remove Brick
      end
    end
  end

  Game -> User: Level Completed
  note right of User: Rule 6
end
@enduml"
}

{
  "output": "@startuml
actor User
participant Game
participant Board
participant Snake
participant Food

User -> Game: Start Game
note right of Game: Rule 7
Game -> Board: Initialize Board with Snake and Food
note right of Board: Rule 6

alt User sets difficulty
  User -> Game: Set difficulty to easy
  note right of Game: Rule 11
  Game -> Snake: Set speed to 0.5 blocks/sec

  User -> Game: Set difficulty to hard
  note right of Game: Rule 11
  Game -> Snake: Set speed to 2 blocks/sec

  note right of Game: Rule 8
  Game -> Snake: Change direction
  Snake -> Board: Move

    Snake -> Snake: Grow by 1 block
    note right of Snake: Rule 3
    Game -> Food: Place new Food
    note right of Food: Rule 9
    Game -> Snake: Increase speed by 1%
    note right of Snake: Rule 10
